CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "Registering - Shown registering are, seated, left to right: 33 degree Masons W.R. Webster, of New Brighton, Pa.; C.F. Rodgers, of East Chicago, Ill., the oldest member in length of service and also a member of the Supreme Council of the Fraternity; C. Allen, of Philadelphia, Grand Keeper of Archives; and, standing: Dr. F.C. Rogan, of Chicago; W.W. Grasty, of Chester, Pa.; D.A. Ford, of PRovidence, R.I., and L.B. Henderson, of Steubenville, Ohio."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven 33 degree Masons, seated from left: W.R. Webster, C.F. Rodgers, and C. Allen; standing from left: Dr. F.C. Rogan, W.W. Grasty, D.A. Ford, and L.B. Henderson, gathered at registration table in Fort Pitt Hotel for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33-Degree Masons
